Acanthus ilicifolius

   [2736.jpg]
    Authority   L.
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Asteridae:Scrophulariales:Acanthaceae
     Synonyms
   Common names mangrove
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 2736

   Notes
   SOURCES
   Tomlinson P 1986 pp 174 [SAL]
   Troup R 1921 pp 693 [DRA, LIMITS]
   Aronson J 1989 pp 1989 [SAL, TEMP]
   National RC 1980 pp 52-54 [DRA, SAL, TEXT, TEMP, KTMP, RAIN, DEP]
   GROWING PERIOD
   Herbaceous perennial shrub.
   COMMON NAMES
   Acanthus.
   FURTHER INF
   Scientific synonym: A. neo-guineensis. It sometimes form a dense
   undergrowth that can be troublesome in wood-cutting operations.
   Photosynthesis pathway C3. Grows up to 2 m tall. Adapted to the
   conditions in mangrove swamps.

   Sources

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
